{
  "text": "The hypoxic bone marrow (with 1%-7% O 2 ) seems to enhance the growth of metastases in the skeleton [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Body tissues under pathophysiological conditions may adapt to limits well under the normoxia (20% O 2 ) [CITATION_3] . Tumor growth occurs also under 1% O 2 , and hypoxia regulates the metabolism including nutrient uptake, utilization, and waste removal [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
